abstract.text: AutomixIQTunedMusicCacheDelegate protocol defines the methods to be implemented with storing and providing cached track data

Broadcast your playlist, mix, or set along with your voice, to the world. Tune in to other broadcasts and jump in the conversation with comments, or show your support with quick reactions. An interactive UI for AutomixIQ.
AutomixIQTrackModel models a track. This metadata is required.
AutomixIQTunedAuthenticationResponse models the response of a Tuned OAuth request
AutomixIQTunedRestDelegate protocol defines the methods to be implemented that will provide AutomixIQ the credentials and identifiers to Tuned Global’s backend
AutomixIQLogLevel is an enum of all the AutomixIQ available log levels
AutomixIQStreamingDelegate protocol defines the methods to be implemented with providing AutomixIQ the information it requires to play content.
AutomixIQPluginMetadataModel models metadata of a track traditionally obtained by running plugins on it. Key and BPM are recommented for best mixing.
The Type entry for bpm and key are “key” and “bpm” (case sensitive) respectively, the values need to be formatted as strings, and the key needs to be in OpenKey format.
AutomixIQStatus models the State of the AutomixIQ during playback.
Availablity of underlying technologies and APIs.
AutomixIQStatusObserverDelegate protocol defines the methods to be implemented with observing the status of AutomixIQ to reflect it on a UI.
AutomixIQ represents the AutomixIQ SDK and exposes all its functionality. It follows a Singleton pattern.
AutomixIQWaveformModel models the waveform of a track.
AutomixIQPlaylistOperation models a move, add or remove operation of a track in a playlist.
